response_recognition: The volunteer holds the nut in her hands which are then tied with the rope. When the magician removes the rope, the nut is no longer in the volunteer's hand but appears in the magician's pocket.
The magician folds the sheet of paper smaller and smaller until it transforms into a pack of cards.
The magician shakes the rubix cube and it becomes all white.
The magician firstly puts the rings around his arms, but after he turns around, the volunteer has them around their arms.
The magician asks the volunteer to mark the cards using the pen. After he shuffles them, the volunteer's writing has disappeared from all of the cards.
The magician places the bread sticks in the bag, when the volunteer looks into the bag the bread sticks have transformed into a bun.
The magician unscrews his own finger and then shakes it back into place.
The magician is able to hide his whole arm inside the blue paper bag.
The magician magically repairs split card.
The magician changes the colour of the leaf several times.
The magician pours water into a cup from the bottle and then pours the water into another cup but when he tips it upside down, no water spills out.
Green and golden sweets fall out of the pages of the book.
